---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { brand } from '../config/brand';
---
<Layout
  title="Make a Payment | Belvedere Decks"
  description="Pay your Belvedere Decks invoice securely online or by check. Payments follow the three-installment schedule in your contract: deposit, project start, and final walkthrough."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Payment Link</p>
      <h1>Make a payment.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        Make secure payments for your deck project easily and conveniently. The
        schedule below is written into your contract before work begins.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid cols-2">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Online Payment</h3>
          <p>Pay securely through our online portal. Fast, easy, and convenient.</p>
          <!-- TODO: point at the payment processor link when it's set up (next step).
               Until then the button is disabled-styled so nothing dead-ends. -->
          <p><a class="btn primary" href="/estimate" aria-disabled="true"
            style="opacity: 0.55; pointer-events: none;">Pay Online (coming soon)</a></p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Pay by Check</h3>
          <p>Prefer to pay by check? Make checks payable to:</p>
          <p><strong>{brand.legalName}</strong><br />
          <span style="color: var(--muted-foreground); font-size: 0.9rem;">Address provided upon contract signing</span></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Payment schedule</h2>
      <p>Our payment structure is designed to be fair and transparent:</p>
      <table class="stack">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>1/3 · At contract signing</th><td>The deposit. This reserves your build slot and covers material ordering.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>1/3 · At project start</th><td>When materials are delivered and work begins.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>1/3 · After final walkthrough</th><td>The final third after substantial completion, when you've walked the finished deck and you're satisfied.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>A note on Maryland law:</strong> home improvement deposits in Maryland are
        capped at one-third of the contract price, and we never ask for final payment
        until the work is substantially complete. If any contractor asks for more up
        front, that's a red flag, ours included.
      </div>

      <h2>Questions about payment?</h2>
      <p>
        Contact us directly for any payment-related questions or to discuss payment
        options: call or text
        <a href={`tel:${brand.phone || brand.phoneDisplay}`}>{brand.phoneDisplay}</a>
        or email <a href={`mailto:${brand.email}`}>{brand.email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
